        },
        {
            "title":"\u25b9 A1. Monument presentation",
            "parades":[
                {
                    "title":"Location",
                    "parent":"A1",
                    "actions":[
                        {
                            "goto":"cam-exterior-distant-river.txt"
                        },
                        {
                            "show-side-text":"Sant Quirze de Pedret is a small mediaeval church in central Catalonia's Bergued\u00e0 area, near the Pyrenees foothills and close to an important old route. The Llobregat River, one of the territory's key waterways, flows nearby.\n<br> <br> <embed src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/mp3/location.mp3' loop='true' autostart='true' height='0'>\n<video controls width='400' class='rounded'><source src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/img/Flying-to-Pedret.mp4' type='video/mp4' /></video> <br>\n<img src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/img/IMG_5615.jpg' width='400' class='rounded'> </img> "
                        },
                        {
                            "enable-pois":[
                                
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "title":"Origin",
                    "parent":"A1",
                    "actions":[
                        {
                            "goto":"cam-exterior-distant-1.txt"
                        },
                        {
                            "show-side-text":"The temple was originally constructed at the end of the ninth century. Its architecture has changed considerably over time, and its walls have been decorated at two different times, with figurative mural paintings.  <br> <br> <img src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/img/phases.png' width='400' class='rounded'> </img> <embed src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/mp3/origin.mp3' loop='true' autostart='true' height='0'>"
                        },
                        {
                            "enable-pois":[
                                
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "title":"First church",
                    "parent":"A1",
                    "actions":[
                        {
                            "goto":"cam-exterior-planta.txt"
                        },
                        {
                            "show-side-text":"The first church had a single nave crowned by a quadrangular vaulted apse. Later, in the middle of the 10th century, it was enlarged with two aisles ending with vaulted horseshoe-shaped apses. The first pictorial decoration was limited, as far as we know, to the back wall of the apse and a wall of the original nave. <br> <br> <img src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/img/phases9-10.png' width='400' class='rounded'> </img> \n\n <embed src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/mp3/first-church.mp3' loop='true' autostart='true' height='0'>"
                        },
                        {
                            "enable-pois":[
                                
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "title":"First decoration",
                    "parent":"A1",
                    "actions":[
                        {
                            "goto":"cam-central-apse.txt"
                        },
                        {
                            "show-side-text":"A crucifixion was depicted on the wall of the nave. The compositions that occupied the background of the apse consist of two medallions housing figures. One of them is a bearded male figure with open arms in a prayerful attitude. The other is a warrior on horseback and the space that contains it is completed with four arms of a cross. Other figures of different proportions complete the composition, which, to date, has not been able to be interpreted. These paintings can be dated to the middle of the 10th or early 11th century.\n<br> <br> <img src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/img/orant-cavaller.jpg' width='400' class='rounded'> </img> \n\n <embed src='https://www.cs.upc.edu/~virtual/mp3/first-decoration.mp3' loop='true' autostart='true' height='0'>"
                        },
                        {
                            "enable-pois":[
                                
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
